Description:
Style, Comfort, Ease
Featuring street frontage in an exceptionally convenient cul-de-sac, moments to cosmopolitan Sydney Road and Coburg Market, this contemporary three bedroom residence flaunts a private northerly courtyard. Presenting an open kitchen/meals/living, plus space to entertain outdoors, it's easy to look after and even easier to enjoy. Boasting stainless steel Blanco appliances and a dishwasher, the kitchen is completed by dark mosaic tiled splashbacks, cupboards and expansive counters. Bright double bedrooms include a spacious ground floor room and two above: one with a walk-in robe and mountain glimpses, and another with built-in robe. The bathroom comes with a relaxing bath, separate shower, toilet and vanity with semi-recessed basin, complemented by a second toilet and full laundry. Further features include panel heaters, split system heating and cooling, a large under stair storage area and automatic garage with interior and courtyard access. A short stroll to trams, trains, reserves, shops, cafes and restaurants, and close to schools, the locale is fittingly attractive too.
Insights: 9A Methven Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
The perfect way to commence
Making a start in property ownership doesn't come any cooler or more desirable than this boutique two bedroom apartment, designed to deliver generous spaces in a cul-de-sac setting of outstanding convenience. A substantial terrace area that's ideal for entertaining or simply enjoying all to yourself precedes the appealing proportions of a living/dining space and an open-plan kitchen equipped with excellent storage, sparkling surfaces and stainless steel appliances. Two double bedrooms, including a main bedroom incorporating built-in robes, share a bathroom defined by significant size and perfect presentation. With the morning sunlight streaming through the living/dining/kitchen windows and the bedrooms warmed by the afternoon sun and Coburg Station, Sydney Road shops, cafes and tram routes all merely moments away - excellent in every way.

Description:
Get Set For A Fantastic Future
Fantastic family living is assured with this welcoming three bedroom plus study home set in a winning locale. A stroll to transport, shops, cafes, local favourite O'Heas Bakery, Harmony Park and Coburg North Primary, and with a bike track right out front, this feature rich family abode includes a sunlit living/meals/kitchen starring stainless steel appliances, including a gas cooktop, fan forced oven and canopy rangehood, teamed with a Miele dishwasher. A sliding door leads to open and covered entertaining areas and a rear garden, linked to a ROW. A formal dining room provides an additional space to share delicious dinners with friends, and the open study is well proportioned. Each of the three double bedrooms offers a BIR/WIR, serviced by a main bathroom, the master boasts ensuite, and you'll benefit from refrigerated cooling, heating, a security system, wide driveway and automatic double garage with direct entry. Around 9 kilometres from the CBD, get set to get the most out of life.

Description:
Contemporary Family Values
With a wealth of space, inside and out, this centrally located four bedroom, two bathroom contemporary residence represents enormous appeal for family homebuyers. Freshly painted, a flexible floor plan includes wide hallway, relaxing lounge, upper level retreat/study space and generous living domain spilling to central, covered courtyard and landscaped surrounds. An open plan kitchen displays modern white appliances, dishwasher, dark counters and large corner pantry. Comfortable accommodation is provided by four bedrooms, including huge main with walk-in-robe, ensuite and balcony. Features built-in-robes, family bathroom, powder room, storage, ducted heating/cooling and automatic double garage/direct internal entry. Nestled in a cul-de-sac, and within walking distance from scenic Coburg Lake, vibrant cafes, continental shops, markets, schools and transport, it offers a safe, convenient lifestyle opportunity.

Description:
Family Oasis of Quality and Class
In a secluded cul-de-sac moments from Merri Creek parkland and trails, this two-storey family home is set to impress with its wonderfully spacious floorplan, outstanding features throughout and delightful gardens all-round. Free-flowing design highlights four upstairs bedrooms (large master with fitted WIR and stylish ensuite), main family bathroom and wide front balcony. Downstairs: light-filled lounge and adjoining dining room (or home office) through to the open-plan family/meals area and granite-bench kitchen with stainless steel appliances and ample cupboard space. Bi-folds (from the living area) reveal a gorgeous back garden complete with undercover entertaining area, water feature and established perimeter trees for added privacy. Add to this ducted heating and evaporative cooling, laundry and guest powder room (third WC), keyless entry, under-stair storeroom, marble-top vanities, double garage with internal entry. Walking distance to Coburg Lake and Merri Creek trails, childcare centre, Coburg High School, close to Sydney Road trams, cafes and Coburg's renowned shops and supermarkets. Position, privacy and inner-urban ease! Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:

A coveted Coburg neighbourhood just north of Brunswick's border sets the scene for this heritage Californian Bungalow providing a lifestyle of immediate family comfort with outstanding options to further enhance and expand (STCA). Enjoyed by generations of the one family since new (around 1930), the home's spotless interior comprises three bedrooms (large master), central bathroom and second WC, front lounge, adjoining dining room and separate kitchen/meals area. Description:
Under Offer
Exceptional design and inclusions make this contemporary three bedroom, two bathroom home something special in the Strathmore College zone. Enhanced by smart and easily maintained surrounds, the home boasts a family room or pool room and an expansive, impeccably equipped kitchen/dining/living showcasing premium 900mm appliances, a waterfall stone island bench and lustrous soft close cabinetry. To the rear is a haven boasting an outdoor spa and covered entertaining area/optional parking with electronic access to a rear ROW. Bedrooms host mirrored BIRs/a WIR, chic, fully tiled bathrooms include an ensuite, plus there's a powder room, ducted vacuum, video intercom, security system and heating/cooling in all bedrooms and living spaces. Shore Reserve, trams, schools and cafes are a stroll away.
Insights: 77 Donne Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Broad In Options And Appeal
Spacious and functional, this four bedroom family home is conveniently placed near schools, Coburg train station and shopping centre plus Melville Road tram and retail junction. Large windows throughout allow volumes of natural light to permeate whilst electronic shutters ensure security and efficient climate control. A large formal lounge/dining area and a casual kitchen/meals/family zone intertwine, separated from the sleeping quarters for maximum privacy. Caesarstone bench tops, a full complement of stainless steel appliances and glass splashbacks define the modern kitchen. Three double bedrooms present elegant rosette ceilings and feature ample built-in wardrobes, the fourth easily repurposing for study. There's also ducted heating, lots of driveway parking plus a double garage with workshop and storeroom/studio. Occupying a generous allotment measuring approximately 560m2, the land may also interest developers or make an excellent new home site (both STCA). Alternatively, investors will appreciate the current return of $450 per week and renovators may like to modernise.
Insights: 18 Davis Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 49 other 4 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Live It Up
You're invited to take your place in fashionable Pentridge Village: three storey, two bedroom townhouse has the modern living areas you'd expect, and ensuites to both bedrooms. Showcasing stainless steel appliances and stone counters, the kitchen flows into an open meals zone which continues into a living area with hardwood flooring. From here a sliding glass door accesses a balcony for alfresco dining. Each bedroom has a built-in or walk-in robe, and further handy features include a powder room, European laundry, good storage space, ducted heating, split system cooling and automated garage with internal access. Stroll to a wide selection of amenities including Merri Creek and surrounding parkland, transport and Coburg Senior High School, with Coburg Market and other lively Sydney Road shops also nearby.
Insights: 60 Woiwurung Crescent, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 58 other 2 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
A Californian Dream In Sought After Street
Superbly located in a quiet tree-lined pocket of family friendly Coburg, this pretty as a picture 1920’s Californian bungalow is a sensitively modernised and extended period residence. Featuring burnished baltic pine floors, ducted heating and fresh decor, it includes two front bedrooms, main with spacious mirrored BIR’s, pristine bathroom, formal lounge with a heritage fireplace and polished timber mantle, air-conditioned dining room, generous timber kitchen, third bedroom, spacious family room, laundry and powder room.
• Excellently positioned in sought after family area
• Modernised Californian Bungalow retaining some period features
• Immaculately presented property with strong street presence
• 2 car lock-up garage plus additional off-street street parking
• Close to shops, schools, transport, with easy Citylink access
From the cultivated front garden to the well sized back-yard with BBQ and double lock-up garage, this delightful family home is an absolute gem with a beautiful street presence, providing excellent proximity to quality schools, local shopping, trams, trains and a rapid CBD commute via Citylink.
Insights: 87 Phillips St, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2017 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.
